window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>For over 30 years, internationally known yoga teacher Tias Little has explored yoga as a spiritual path, and here he offers key teachings from his journey that will resonate with anyone who has dedicated themselves to a mind-body discipline.</p> <p>Little synthesizes years of integrated study in classical yoga, Sanskrit, Buddhist studies, somatic practices, anatomy, massage, and trauma healing, and offers a multifaceted and holistic perspective on yoga practice. He shares his struggles and joys as a yogi and chronicles the transformation of his understanding and practice along the way. </p> <p>Each chapter is a lesson, and he includes companion practices such as poses, reflections, meditations, and explorations to help you embody the teachings. Little weaves together poetic metaphor, clear instruction, compassion, and humor, bringing the teachings alive in an intimate yet immediate way.</p>"; 
